                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13495746" author="arkin" created="Mon, 12 Nov 2012 23:26:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attached proposed fix and related test updates.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13495859" author="garydgregory" created="Tue, 13 Nov 2012 02:13:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The only length 32 restriction I see in &lt;a href=&quot;https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5424&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5424&lt;/a&gt; is &quot;The &quot;swVersion&quot; parameter is a string.  It MUST NOT be longer than 32  characters.&quot; What am I missing?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13495932" author="ralph.goers@dslextreme.com" created="Tue, 13 Nov 2012 04:23:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Take a look at section 6.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;PARAM_NAME is of type SD_NAME which is 1*32PRINTUSASCII (1-32 US ASCII printable characters). Right now we are only validating the length, not the characters.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also note that HOSTNAME, APP-NAME, PROCID and MSGID also have length restrictions.  However PARAM_VALUE does not.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13495964" author="ralph.goers@dslextreme.com" created="Tue, 13 Nov 2012 05:05:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The patch was applied although the test had to be modified slightly as it didn&apos;t incorporate the new memo item that was added. Please verify and close.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
